reviewText: Firstly, if you're a collector of vintage TV material, you'll be getting a very respectable chunk of wide-ranging shows in this set.  The quality is quite acceptable (public domain of course) but all very watchable.  25 DVDs in glossy paper sleeves, stored in a solid DVD box.  Even at the full list price this set is a super bargain. reviewText: For the price, you can't beat the value! Most of the shows are a treat to view after so many decades. All of the shows are an historical reflection of that halycon era  before the grisly JFK assassination, exuding values that Baby Boomers were raised to emulate.  While many of the shows can crack one up into guffaws of laughter, some of the earliest productions are tedious, to say the least. Nevertheless, anyone who buys this collation of old TV shows will get more than enough entertainment to justify the price. Moreover, you will get a better idea of what series, if any, you'd like to purchase in their entirety.
summary: GREAT VALUE FOR CONNOISSEURS OF OLD TV SHOWS

reviewText: I always enjoy looking back at tv shows and go on a nostalgia trip of yesteryear when I was young and only had a b&w tv. I wish the Rin Tin Tin series was when he was in the calvery instead of the '40's collection here. The othere were great though. Some in color, like the Lucy series. All in all, an enjoying dvd.

reviewText: I got this for my next door neighbor.  He loves everything retro.  Every time I see him he stops to thank me for this DVD.  I guess it was 5 stars for him, and for all he does for me (including dog sitting while I'm away), it was worth the price.
